<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 26, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Rebalanced five shared public articles whose URLs read as multi-species but whose body and FAQ schema were still internally dog-coded. The fix was additive: kept the dog framing where a dog breeder genuinely benefits from it, and added explicit goat, sheep, and horse parity in every section that was making a general claim about how breeding programs work.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Articles updated</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li><a href="/articles/breeder-crm" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Breeder CRM</a>. FAQ schema rewritten for livestock; body rebalanced so waitlists, buyer matching, and migration steps span litters, kiddings, foalings, lambings, and kindlings. Added <a href="/compare/best-goat-breeding-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/compare/best-goat-breeding-software</a> as a peer link to the existing dog comparison.</li>
    <li><a href="/articles/breeder-communication-platforms" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Breeder Communication Platforms</a>. Body rebalanced so waitlist updates, repeat-question templates, and integration-with-breeding-records examples include kidding/foaling alongside whelping. The seven-platform table is unchanged because the underlying tools really do focus on dogs where they say they do.</li>
    <li><a href="/articles/cloud-breeder-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Cloud-Based Breeder Software</a>. Six body sections rebalanced. Whelping area paired with kidding pen; rearing protocols now contrast dog-side (ENS, ESI, Volhard PAT) with goat-side (CD&amp;T, disbudding, FAMACHA scoring, weaning weights) and horse-side (halter training, farrier visits). Contract example now includes a paired CAE-management clause alongside the existing spay/neuter clause.</li>
    <li><a href="/articles/buyer-application-tools" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Buyer Application Tools</a>. FAQ schema entry on multi-species rewritten to enumerate species-specific questions (pasture, fencing, FAMACHA literacy, biosecurity intent for mixed-status herds). Screening categories now include pasture acreage, perimeter fencing, and intended role (dairy, fiber, meat, brush control, 4-H / FFA project) alongside the dog-side framing.</li>
    <li><a href="/articles/breeding-management-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Breeding Management Software</a>. Deep rebalance. Added a goat-side five-step breeding workflow (heat detection, CIDR / buck effect / lighting triggers, service date, ultrasound confirmation, expected kidding date) alongside the existing dog-side five-step progesterone workflow. Added a full goat-side rearing-protocol bullet list (CD&amp;T, disbudding, structured tattoo placement, FAMACHA / FEC / FECRT, weaning weight). FAQ schema gained a goat-and-sheep-specific Q. Registry, marketplace, and how-to-choose sections now name ADGA, AGS, NDGA, AQHA, ARBA, and the herd-health passport.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">What was intentionally left alone</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The four dog-targeted puppy-* and litter-* articles still exist and are still dog-coded. They are real SEO surfaces for real dog-buyer queries that goat buyers do not have. The goat-side peers shipped in the previous slice (<a href="/articles/goat-kid-health-guarantee-what-it-covers" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">goat-kid health guarantee</a>, <a href="/articles/goat-kid-deposit-and-sale-terms" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">goat-kid deposit and sale terms</a>, <a href="/articles/dairy-goat-record-keeping-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">dairy goat record-keeping</a>, <a href="/articles/goat-herd-health-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">goat herd-health</a>, <a href="/articles/goat-kidding-tracking-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">goat kidding tracking</a>) are the right parity, not rewrites of the dog-targeted pieces.</p>

  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Status doc: <code>docs/research/goat-audit/2026-05-25/demo-execution/next-18-shared-public-article-rebalance-status.md</code> in the <code>breederhq</code> repo.</p>
